{
  "type": "PrimaryTheme",
  "number": 4696,
  "title": "yoke",
  "comment": "The wooden collar which joins two animals, usually oxen, to enable them to pull together. Used metaphorically the term may denote the partnership of those who share a yoke or, more usually, the subjection of those under a yoke. As his covenant partners God's people are yoked to him and he will break the oppressive yoke of their enemies.",
